S uper Eagles and Leicester of England midfielder, Wilfred Ndidi, has resumed training after his surgery penultimate week. The Nigerian has been out of action since picking up a knee injury in training ahead of the Foxes’ League Cup fixture against Aston Villa. He will miss today’s Premier League match against Burnley, the third game he won’t be available for selection since he suffered a training ground injury. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Ndidi has taken a step forward in his recovery and was snapped training with the rest of his teammates, including Kelechi Iheaancho, at Belvoir Drive on Friday. In his absence, the Foxes were unable to beat Southampton and Villa. Coach Brendan Rodgers has, however, provided a positive fitness update, saying that Ndidi has made great progress; he’s out on training pitch working.